title: KSL.com college football Players of the Week (Week 8)
text:
SALT LAKE CITY Â— After strong wins in previous weeks, both Utah and Utah State had a setback last weekend as the two programs went on the road and got beat by double digits. 
The Utes came into Saturday's game as the third-ranked team and an underdog to USC. The Trojans, though, took control of the game and never looked back as Utah suffered its first loss of the season. The Aggies hoped to continue its winning streak after drubbing Boise State, but found themselves on the losing end of rough night. And BYU took care of business against a weak FCS team, hanging 70 points on the Seahawks.
